  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The CPB device is deployed in operating theatres where ambient temperature ranges from 18°C to 26°C, perfusionist bay electromagnetic interference from electrosurgical units is routine, and altitude-related pressure variation (0.85–1.01 atm) occurs across facility types. Validation activities were conducted exclusively at 22°C, 1.0 atm atmospheric pressure in a controlled laboratory; no environmental-sensitivity study was performed and no operating envelope bounding the thermal, pressure, or EMI parameters is linked to this package.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
